      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">What's new</h1>

      <div>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Release notes: 8 September 2020</h2>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">New feature</h3>
        <p>Case information pages for POM and SPO users now identify recall cases. If a case
          is a recall you will see a 'Recall' badge.</p>

        <p>OMiC policy rules for recall cases have been applied to these cases. </p>

        <p>Notify us of any issues you find by using the 'Contact us'
          form which is linked to at the bottom of every page.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Release notes: 23 November 2020</h2>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">New feature</h3>
        <p>Victim liaison officer details can now be manually added to
          the profile of the prisoner, you’ll find this under
          VICTIM LIAISON OFFICER (VLO) section of the page.</p>

        <p>You are able to add, edit and delete these entries plus make multiple
          contacts if required. Notify us of any issues you find by using the
          'Contact us' form which is linked to at the bottom of every page. </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Release notes: DD November 2020</h2>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">New feature</h3>
        <p>From the prisoner profile page in Manage POM cases service,
          Prison Offender Managers can now complete early allocation referrals.
          You are able to complete an assessment at any time throughout a sentence,
          and send the referral to the community from 18 months before release. </p>

        <p>More Information on the early allocation process can be found in EQUIP
          by clicking <a href ='https://equip-portal.rocstac.com/CtrlWebIsapi.dll/?__id=webDiagram.show&map=0%3A9A63E167DE4B400EA07F81A9271E1944&dgm=4F984B45CBC447B1A304B2FFECABB777'>here</a>
          and searching for ‘early allocation’.  </p>
      </div>
